    "faq": {
      "type": "lsc-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What exactly does a Hydrofacial do for my skin?",
            "answer": "<p>HydroFacial is a multi-step medical-grade treatment that deeply cleanses, exfoliates, extracts congestion, and infuses the skin with targeted hydrating serums. It improves texture, clarity, and hydration in a single session while supporting overall skin health.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is there any downtime afterwards?",
            "answer": "<p>No. HydroFacial requires no downtime. You may experience mild redness immediately after treatment, which typically settles within a few hours. Most patients return to normal activities straight away.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Will it hurt or feel uncomfortable?",
            "answer": "<p>HydroFacial is generally described as comfortable and gentle. The vortex technology uses light suction to remove impurities without squeezing or manual pressure. Most patients find it relaxing.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How often should I have a HydroFacial?",
            "answer": "<p>For maintenance, many patients choose treatment every 4–6 weeks. If addressing specific concerns such as congestion or dullness, a short course may be recommended before moving to maintenance sessions.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What skin concerns does HydroFacial help with?",
            "answer": "<p>HydroFacial can help improve dullness, dehydration, congestion, enlarged pores, uneven texture, and mild acne. It is also commonly used before events for an immediate skin refresh.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How is HydroFacial different from a regular facial?",
            "answer": "<p>Unlike traditional facials, HydroFacial uses medical-grade vortex technology to exfoliate and extract impurities without manual squeezing. It delivers controlled, consistent results in a clinical environment.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_7": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long do results last?",
            "answer": "<p>You will notice immediate improvement in hydration and glow. Results typically last several weeks, depending on your skin type, lifestyle, and skincare routine. Regular treatments support longer-term skin clarity and texture improvement.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_8": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is HydroFacial suitable for sensitive or acne prone skin?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. The treatment can be tailored to suit sensitive, congested, or acne-prone skin. The gentle exfoliation and vacuum-assisted extraction help clear pores without causing trauma. Suitability is confirmed during consultation.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_9": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is HydroFacial safe during pregnancy?",
            "answer": "<p>HydroFacial is generally considered safe, but certain active ingredients may be avoided during pregnancy. Please inform us during consultation so the treatment can be adjusted appropriately.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_10": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How bad is the downtime, really?",
            "answer": "<p>Expect 2-3 days of redness like a strong sunburn, followed by light peeling on days 4-5. You can typically wear makeup by day 6.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_11": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I wear makeup straight after?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Makeup can usually be applied the same day if desired. However, many patients prefer to leave the skin makeup-free to enjoy the natural post-treatment glow.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_12": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What payment options do you offer?",
            "answer": "<p>We offer flexible payment options to make your treatment as convenient as possible. You can choose to pay per single session or pay in full for a course of treatments for better overall value. We accept card, cash, and bank transfer in clinic.</p><p>For added flexibility, we also offer 0% finance through Klarna, allowing you to spread the cost into manageable instalments with a range of payment options available, subject to eligibility.</p><p>If you’re unsure which option is best for you, our team will be happy to guide you.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_13": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is the difference between a Full Hydrafacial and an Express Hydrafacial?",
            "answer": "<p>The Express Hydrofacial is a quicker, more streamlined version of the treatment. It focuses on the first three core cleansing and exfoliating steps of the full seven-step Hydrofacial, giving your skin a refreshed, cleansed boost in roughly half the time.</p><p>The Full Hydrofacial includes all seven steps for deeper rejuvenation, enhanced hydration and maximum glow.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_14": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is your cancellation policy?",
            "answer": "<p>Cancellations up to 24 hours before your appointment will receive a full refund or can be rescheduled.<br/><br/>Any cancellations on the day can be rescheduled but will not be refunded.<br/><br/>If you do not show to your appointment you will not receive a refund or a reschedule. Please note that we offer email and text appointment reminders right up until 24 hours before your appointment.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_15": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What makes HydroFacial different from a regular facial?",
            "answer": "<p>Unlike a traditional facial, HydroFacial delivers consistent, medical-grade results using advanced technology rather than manual extractions.</p><p>It penetrates deeper into the skin to remove debris from pores and replenish essential moisture all with no irritation, no downtime, and visible results after a single treatment.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_16": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "I would like to speak to someone before I book my treatment, how is best to do this?",
            "answer": "<p>If you would like to speak to someone please do one of the below<br/><br/>- Use the enquiry button.<br/>- Contact us via email - info@laserskinclinics.co.uk<br/>- Call us during opening hours on 01902 256667<br/>- Send us a WhatsApp by clicking the WhatsApp button on the website.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_17": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Who is HydroFacial suitable for?",
            "answer": "<p>HydroFacial is safe for all skin types and tones — even sensitive skin.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_18": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is there any downtime?",
            "answer": "<p>There’s no downtime whatsoever.</p><p>You might notice a slight pink glow for an hour or two, but you can return to your normal activities straight away, it’s even safe to have a HydroFacial on the same day as an event.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_19": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long does the treatment take?",
            "answer": "<p>A typical HydroFacial takes 30 to 1 hour, making it perfect for a lunchtime treatment or quick pick-me-up before a night out.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_20": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How often should I have a HydroFacial?",
            "answer": "<p>For ongoing skin health and radiance, we recommend a HydroFacial every 4 to 6 weeks.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_21": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Does it hurt?",
            "answer": "<p>Not at all. HydroFacial is completely comfortable and non-invasive.</p><p>Most clients describe it as a gentle, cooling sensation with light suction - relaxing and refreshing, rather than painful.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
